{"title": "Russia says F-16 transfer to Ukraine would raise questions of Nato\u2019s involvement", "tags": "world", "timestamp": "2023-05-22", "content": "MOSCOW \u2013 The transfer of F-16 fighter jets to Ukraine would raise the question of Nato\u2019s involvement in the conflict, Russia\u2019s Ambassador to the United States Anatoly Antonov said in remarks published early on Monday.\n\u201cThere is no infrastructure for the operation of the F-16 in Ukraine and the needed number of pilots and maintenance staff is not there either,\u201d Mr Antonov said in remarks published on the embassy\u2019s Telegram messaging channel.\n\u201cWhat will happen if the American fighters take off from Nato airfields, controlled by foreign \u2018volunteers\u2019?\u201c\nUS President Joe Biden on Friday endorsed training programmes for Ukrainian pilots on F-16 fighter jets, and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky assured Mr Biden that the aircraft would not be used to go into Russian territory.\nMr Antonov said that any Ukrainian strike on Crimea would be considered a strike on Russia.\n\u201cIt is important that the US be fully aware of the Russian response,\u201d Mr Antonov said."}